A pedestrian is in critical condition after being hit by an SUV in Columbia Heights on Saturday night. At about 9 p.m., a man was crossing Central Avenue on foot near 45th Avenue Northeast when a southbound SUV hit him, according to the Anoka County Sheriff's Office. The man was brought by ambulance to a local hospital where he was in critical condition. The sheriff's office, Columbia Heights Police Department and Minnesota State Patrol are investigating.